Installing the Job Search Browser Extension
This document provides step-by-step instructions for installing the Job Search Browser Extension, which allows users to search old and new job documents. The extension is stored on SharePoint.

Prerequisites
Access to the SharePoint path where the extension is stored.
Administrative permissions to install browser extensions.
Steps to Install the Extension
1. Download the Extension
Open your browser and navigate to the SharePoint path where the extension is stored.
Locate the extension file (usually a .zip or .crx file).
Download the extension file to your local machine.
2. Enable Developer Mode (Chrome)
Open Google Chrome.
Click on the three vertical dots in the upper right corner of the browser to open the menu.
Navigate to More tools > Extensions.
Toggle the Developer mode switch in the upper right corner.
3. Install the Extension
If the Extension is a .zip File
Extract the .zip file to a folder on your local machine.
In the Extensions page of Chrome (with Developer mode enabled), click on the Load unpacked button.
Select the folder where you extracted the .zip file.
The extension will be installed and appear in the list of installed extensions.
If the Extension is a .crx File
Drag and drop the .crx file onto the Extensions page in Chrome.
Confirm the installation by clicking on the Add extension button in the prompt that appears.
4. Verify Installation
Ensure the extension appears in the list of installed extensions.
The extension icon should also appear in the toolbar, next to the address bar.
5. Configure the Extension (if necessary)
Click on the extension icon in the toolbar.
Follow any prompts to configure settings specific to your job document searches.
6. Test the Extension
Open the extension by clicking its icon.
Enter a search query to verify that it can search old and new job documents as expected.
Troubleshooting
Extension not appearing in the toolbar: Ensure Developer mode is enabled and try reinstalling the extension.
Search not functioning correctly: Check the SharePoint path and ensure the extension settings are configured properly.
